article.headline: Old Dominion 64, S. Carolina St. 54
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Abdi Lidonde scored a career-high 20 points to lead Old Dominion to a 64-54 victory Sunday over South Carolina State. Lidonde was 6-of-12, and 6-of-10 from three-point range. His previous high total was 15 points, scored against North Carolina in 2003. The Bulldogs (0-2) pulled within two in the first half, at 15:04 and again at 12:44, when it was 41-39, but baskets by Sam Harris, Jonathan Adams and Brandon Johnson put Old Dominion up by 8 points. Outrebounded by the Monarchs, the Bulldogs couldn't get closer than 57-51 at the 4:34 mark. Harris scored eight points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Monarchs (1-0). Adams also had nine rebounds. Jason Johnson led South Carolina State with 13 points and seven rebounds.
